Sshalias is a script to generate a ssh-client config file with an alias.


Examples
---------

sshalias.py myalias myusername example.com
sshalias.py myalias myusername 127.0.0.1
sshalias.py myalias myusername 192.168.0.1 -v

# You can access the server using this syntax then
ssh myalias


Installing for all users
---------
chmod a+x sshalias.py
sudo mv sshalias.py /usr/bin/


Uninstalling
---------
sudo rm /usr/bin/sshalias.py 
